1
00:00:35,679 --> 00:00:36,280
Move!

2
00:00:44,200 --> 00:00:44,479
Hurry!

3
00:00:44,479 --> 00:00:45,280
Old Lu, help!

4
00:00:45,840 --> 00:00:46,759
Hold it back, quick!

5
00:00:46,759 --> 00:00:48,880
What's with this giant snake?

6
00:00:48,880 --> 00:00:50,240
We didn't provoke it.

7
00:00:50,240 --> 00:00:51,799
Why's it coming after us?

8
00:00:52,119 --> 00:00:54,520
Big guy, if a stranger barged into your home,

9
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:55,399
would you like it?

10
00:00:56,359 --> 00:00:58,880
A prehistoric python came back to life.

11
00:00:59,399 --> 00:01:00,439
The biggest snake in the world

12
00:01:00,479 --> 00:01:01,759
is the Amazon anaconda.

13
00:01:01,759 --> 00:01:03,119
But the longest is only ten meters.

14
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:04,760
Something this big...

15
00:01:04,840 --> 00:01:06,000
Only the Titanoboa comes close.

16
00:01:06,480 --> 00:01:07,680
But it went extinct

17
00:01:07,680 --> 00:01:08,640
58 million years ago.

18
00:01:09,200 --> 00:01:10,359
How could one appear here?

19
00:01:10,439 --> 00:01:11,079
If we really are

20
00:01:11,079 --> 00:01:12,359
getting closer to the Lingxiao Pearl,

21
00:01:12,359 --> 00:01:14,560
based on what we've theorized about it,

22
00:01:14,560 --> 00:01:15,480
the creatures here

23
00:01:15,760 --> 00:01:17,159
having genetic mutations isn't impossible.

24
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:18,840
Genetic mutations again, huh?

25
00:01:22,040 --> 00:01:22,959
Come take a look.

26
00:01:39,159 --> 00:01:39,959
Gold.

27
00:01:40,159 --> 00:01:40,840
Silver.

28
00:01:41,319 --> 00:01:42,120
Iron.

29
00:01:42,519 --> 00:01:43,319
Tin.

30
00:01:44,760 --> 00:01:45,359
Copper.

31
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:46,480
Lead.

32
00:01:47,159 --> 00:01:47,959
Amalgam.

33
00:01:48,400 --> 00:01:49,560
What are these for?

34
00:01:51,640 --> 00:01:52,439
These...

35
00:02:05,159 --> 00:02:06,319
These metal plates

36
00:02:06,640 --> 00:02:07,920
all have magnets inside.

37
00:02:08,960 --> 00:02:10,039
Beneath this stone altar,

38
00:02:10,039 --> 00:02:11,080
there must be a magnet.

39
00:02:11,319 --> 00:02:13,639
Like static contacts in an EM switch,

40
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:16,199
using magnetism to keep it attached.

41
00:02:16,479 --> 00:02:18,000
This disc is like a lock,

42
00:02:18,080 --> 00:02:19,479
and the metal plates are the keys.

43
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:22,159
It's like an electromagnetic switch.

44
00:02:22,439 --> 00:02:23,360
We just need to place the keys

45
00:02:23,360 --> 00:02:24,560
in their corresponding spots,

46
00:02:24,800 --> 00:02:25,919
and we can unlock the mechanism.

47
00:02:26,240 --> 00:02:27,639
If we can solve the mechanism,

48
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,199
we can light up the lamps.

49
00:02:30,120 --> 00:02:32,319
And if all three lamps light up, then...

50
00:02:32,319 --> 00:02:34,039
We can break free from all suffering.

51
00:02:35,199 --> 00:02:36,599
Then hurry up and solve it!

52
00:02:36,599 --> 00:02:37,400
What's the rush?

53
00:02:37,599 --> 00:02:39,159
Can't you see Old Chen is thinking?

54
00:02:39,159 --> 00:02:40,080
Don't disturb him.

55
00:02:40,240 --> 00:02:41,240
But Commander Chen,

56
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,240
you'd better hurry up.

57
00:02:42,240 --> 00:02:43,360
I can't hold it much longer!

58
00:02:51,199 --> 00:02:52,560
These are alchemy symbols,

59
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:53,439
representing metals.

60
00:02:53,719 --> 00:02:55,000
This makes it easier to read.

61
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:57,919
These symbols

62
00:02:58,479 --> 00:03:00,199
are from astrology.

63
00:03:00,560 --> 00:03:01,599
And this pattern

64
00:03:01,919 --> 00:03:03,439
must be a star chart.

65
00:03:04,199 --> 00:03:05,639
It represents the relative motion

66
00:03:05,639 --> 00:03:06,800
of the universe when you were born.

67
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:08,280
Now it all connects.

68
00:03:08,919 --> 00:03:10,039
Gold is the Sun.

69
00:03:10,159 --> 00:03:10,960
Silver is the Moon.

70
00:03:11,039 --> 00:03:12,319
Amalgam is Mercury.

71
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:13,280
Copper is Venus.

72
00:03:13,560 --> 00:03:14,520
Iron is Mars.

73
00:03:14,520 --> 00:03:15,280
Tin is Jupiter.

74
00:03:15,560 --> 00:03:16,479
Lead is Saturn.

75
00:03:16,719 --> 00:03:17,879
That's the Seven Luminaries!

76
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:18,240
Right.

77
00:03:18,240 --> 00:03:19,800
The seven key stars in ancient calendars.

78
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:23,400
Only time and the universe are eternal.

79
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:26,400
Could it be telling us to take the time

80
00:03:26,400 --> 00:03:27,599
inscribed on the altar,

81
00:03:27,919 --> 00:03:29,719
along with the seven planets' positions,

82
00:03:30,039 --> 00:03:31,680
and display it as a star map?

83
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:33,520
The degrees of the zenith

84
00:03:33,520 --> 00:03:35,000
equal the tangent of the meridian's RA,

85
00:03:35,280 --> 00:03:37,039
divided by the cosine of the obliquity,

86
00:03:37,039 --> 00:03:38,120
taken as the arctangent.

87
00:03:38,840 --> 00:03:40,919
We're at 80 degrees East longitude.

88
00:03:41,360 --> 00:03:43,039
The time, as the inscription states,

89
00:03:43,039 --> 00:03:44,400
is December 12th, 9 o'clock.

90
00:03:45,280 --> 00:03:47,599
Obliquity is 23 degrees, 27 minutes.

91
00:03:48,000 --> 00:03:49,960
First, we calculate sidereal time.

92
00:03:51,000 --> 00:03:53,159
S equals local mean time,

93
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:56,639
plus sidereal time at UT zero,

94
00:03:57,039 --> 00:03:59,960
plus Greenwich mean time multiplied by μ.

95
00:04:00,400 --> 00:04:03,159
μ equals 365.84.

96
00:04:25,639 --> 00:04:26,319
Follow this.

97
00:04:31,240 --> 00:04:33,319
Copper, gold.

98
00:04:37,839 --> 00:04:38,480
Silver.

99
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:44,600
Amalgam.

100
00:04:57,160 --> 00:04:57,839
Look at that!

101
00:05:05,839 --> 00:05:06,519
It's lit up!

102
00:05:07,639 --> 00:05:08,480
The lamps are lit!

103
00:05:16,680 --> 00:05:17,319
I get it now.

104
00:05:17,560 --> 00:05:19,040
These lamps and the braziers outside

105
00:05:19,040 --> 00:05:20,240
are all sealed with flammable gas.

106
00:05:20,240 --> 00:05:21,600
Solving the mechanism triggered

107
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:23,000
the linkage system inside the mountain,

108
00:05:23,600 --> 00:05:25,639
opening the gas chambers of both.

109
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:26,680
Once exposed to air and heat,

110
00:05:26,680 --> 00:05:27,959
they ignite on their own.

111
00:05:28,279 --> 00:05:29,279
We're on the right track now.

112
00:05:29,279 --> 00:05:30,120
Two lamps left.

113
00:05:30,120 --> 00:05:31,160
Once they're all lit,

114
00:05:31,160 --> 00:05:32,519
the Lingxiao Pearl should appear.

115
00:05:33,079 --> 00:05:33,920
Next target:

116
00:05:34,439 --> 00:05:35,240
the southern cave.

117
00:05:35,240 --> 00:05:35,879
Right.

118
00:05:37,360 --> 00:05:38,959
Old White-Hair, hand me the crossbow.

119
00:05:40,319 --> 00:05:41,240
Or why don't you go?

120
00:05:47,639 --> 00:05:48,959
It's just an oversized snake.

121
00:05:49,759 --> 00:05:51,800
Master Fatty will cook it up for dinner.

122
00:05:52,759 --> 00:05:53,399
Let's move.

123
00:05:54,439 --> 00:05:56,199
One, two, three!

124
00:06:49,399 --> 00:06:50,639
You guys head to the southern cave.

125
00:06:50,639 --> 00:06:51,720
I'll go help Old Chen.

126
00:07:10,279 --> 00:07:12,079
Old Chen, hurry up!

127
00:07:20,199 --> 00:07:21,000
Move it!

128
00:07:25,120 --> 00:07:26,000
Close the door!

129
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:31,279
Brother Chen, look.

130
00:07:32,000 --> 00:07:33,519
These seven metal pieces

131
00:07:33,519 --> 00:07:35,439
are identical to the ones in that cave.

132
00:07:35,839 --> 00:07:37,720
Do they point to the seven stars again?

133
00:07:39,000 --> 00:07:40,399
The last one was fine, but...

134
00:07:40,600 --> 00:07:41,720
this rectangular one,

135
00:07:41,720 --> 00:07:42,959
what the hell is this supposed to be?

136
00:07:43,279 --> 00:07:46,120
They say heaven is round, earth is square.

137
00:07:46,319 --> 00:07:48,720
So could this be referring to the earth?

138
00:07:49,519 --> 00:07:52,000
Starting from here, counter-clockwise,

139
00:07:52,240 --> 00:07:53,519
these are the twelve palaces.

140
00:07:54,120 --> 00:07:55,600
And based on our earlier calculations,

141
00:07:55,720 --> 00:07:56,959
shift it back twenty-four degrees.

142
00:08:25,600 --> 00:08:26,879
It's lit! They're all lit!

143
00:08:26,879 --> 00:08:28,600
Even the second-level braziers lit up.

144
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,600
Victory is within reach!

145
00:08:29,600 --> 00:08:30,720
Just one mechanism left.

146
00:08:30,720 --> 00:08:31,399
Same as before.

147
00:08:31,399 --> 00:08:31,759
Go!

148
00:08:31,759 --> 00:08:32,399
Move!

149
00:08:34,759 --> 00:08:36,519
Go, one, two, three!

150
00:08:52,559 --> 00:08:53,200
We're done for!

151
00:08:53,360 --> 00:08:54,600
There's no door in this place!

152
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:56,000
Trapped in such a tiny space,

153
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:57,600
if that snake gets in, just the few of us

154
00:08:57,600 --> 00:08:59,120
won't even make a decent meal for it!

155
00:08:59,120 --> 00:09:00,240
Old Lu, quit your damn yelling.

156
00:09:00,879 --> 00:09:02,320
I'll yell all I want!

157
00:09:02,799 --> 00:09:03,600
Commander Chen,

158
00:09:04,000 --> 00:09:04,879
you solve your puzzles.

159
00:09:05,159 --> 00:09:06,080
I don't understand any of it anyway.

160
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:08,080
Master Fatty's gonna go walk that snake.

161
00:09:08,080 --> 00:09:08,799
Be careful!

162
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:09,320
Don't worry.

163
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,440
I can't bear to die before you do.

164
00:09:10,440 --> 00:09:11,399
Here, Old White-Hair.

165
00:09:11,480 --> 00:09:12,279
Let's go.

166
00:09:12,440 --> 00:09:13,240
Move!

167
00:09:18,000 --> 00:09:18,799
Over here!

168
00:09:22,759 --> 00:09:23,360
Hurry!

169
00:09:29,279 --> 00:09:31,039
Old Chen, we've traveled the whole world,

170
00:09:31,120 --> 00:09:32,399
looks like we're back in China.

171
00:09:32,559 --> 00:09:33,399
Isn't this what you use

172
00:09:33,399 --> 00:09:34,799
on that compass of yours?

173
00:09:34,799 --> 00:09:36,799
No mistake. It's an old Chinese star map.

174
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:41,000
Guolao Xingzong, 7 Governors, 4 Remainders

175
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,799
28 constellations as the longitude,

176
00:09:44,519 --> 00:09:45,799
7 Governors and 4 Remainders as latitude.

177
00:09:45,879 --> 00:09:48,679
The Seven are Sun, Moon, and 5 elements.

178
00:09:49,039 --> 00:09:50,720
The Four Remainders are Ziqi,

179
00:09:50,720 --> 00:09:52,240
Yuebo, Luohou, and Jidu.

180
00:09:52,399 --> 00:09:53,279
Interwoven together,

181
00:09:53,279 --> 00:09:55,679
they form a flat version of the star map.

182
00:09:56,639 --> 00:09:58,039
Yichou, Gengchen,

183
00:09:58,440 --> 00:10:00,000
Wuwu, hour of Wu.

184
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:01,759
Sun is in the You palace,

185
00:10:02,279 --> 00:10:03,720
so place Wu on You,

186
00:10:03,720 --> 00:10:04,879
Wei on Xu,

187
00:10:05,440 --> 00:10:06,480
Shen on Hai,

188
00:10:06,879 --> 00:10:08,000
You on Zi,

189
00:10:08,279 --> 00:10:08,960
Xu on Chou,

190
00:10:08,960 --> 00:10:09,879
Hai on Yin,

191
00:10:10,279 --> 00:10:11,360
Zi on Mao,

192
00:10:11,440 --> 00:10:12,440
Chou on Chen,

193
00:10:13,399 --> 00:10:14,519
Yin on Si.

194
00:10:15,039 --> 00:10:15,840
That's it!

195
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,679
It's lit! It's lit, Old Chen!

196
00:10:30,720 --> 00:10:31,519
We did it!

197
00:11:24,639 --> 00:11:25,600
The Lingxiao Pearl!

198
00:11:51,559 --> 00:11:52,360
Brother Chen,

199
00:11:52,399 --> 00:11:54,279
I don't think this is gonna work.

200
00:11:54,279 --> 00:11:55,360
If we don't finish it off,

201
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:57,600
none of us can get the Lingxiao Pearl.

202
00:11:58,000 --> 00:11:59,759
Easy for you to say.

203
00:11:59,879 --> 00:12:00,679
Finish it off?

204
00:12:01,200 --> 00:12:02,559
How are we supposed to finish this thing?

205
00:12:02,840 --> 00:12:04,320
Hit its vital spot.

206
00:12:04,440 --> 00:12:05,919
Strike the snake's heart.

207
00:12:06,360 --> 00:12:09,000
Thing is, this guy's vital spot is hidden.

208
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:10,720
How do we even hit it now?

209
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,279
Try the eyes.

210
00:12:12,440 --> 00:12:13,519
Yes, yes, yes.

211
00:12:14,639 --> 00:12:15,720
Hit its eyes.

212
00:12:15,720 --> 00:12:17,600
Blind it, then it can't see us.

213
00:12:17,639 --> 00:12:18,440
Uncle Min,

214
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:20,240
stop throwing out random ideas, okay?

215
00:12:21,159 --> 00:12:23,480
A snake's vision is poor to begin with.

216
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:26,399
They only see moving objects up close.

217
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:28,559
It's useless, why bother hitting it?

218
00:12:28,919 --> 00:12:29,720
Then how come this guy

219
00:12:29,720 --> 00:12:31,200
keeps following us like this?

220
00:12:31,480 --> 00:12:33,039
Because even if you blind it,

221
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:34,519
it can still see us.

222
00:12:35,080 --> 00:12:36,279
What... what do you mean?

223
00:12:37,080 --> 00:12:38,840
It senses through infrared.

224
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:41,679
Its pit organ is just a thin membrane.

225
00:12:41,840 --> 00:12:42,879
That's its heat-sensing eye.

226
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,360
The outer layer is a heat collector.

227
00:12:45,879 --> 00:12:47,080
Once it encounters a warm object,

228
00:12:47,639 --> 00:12:49,200
the infrared passes through here

229
00:12:49,279 --> 00:12:50,600
to reach the other side of the membrane.

230
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:54,240
So its nerves sense the temp difference,

231
00:12:54,360 --> 00:12:55,639
then generate a bioelectric current

232
00:12:55,639 --> 00:12:56,840
that reaches the snake's brain.

233
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:59,200
So even if you turn off all the lights,

234
00:12:59,200 --> 00:13:00,480
it can still see us.

235
00:13:01,360 --> 00:13:02,759
However, this heat-eye

236
00:13:02,759 --> 00:13:04,960
is also the snake's weakest spot.

237
00:13:05,720 --> 00:13:06,720
Then that's easy.

238
00:13:06,879 --> 00:13:08,600
We blind its heat-eyes first,

239
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:09,799
then strike its vital spot.

240
00:13:09,960 --> 00:13:10,600
Right?

241
00:13:20,679 --> 00:13:22,919
It's here to guard the Lingxiao Pearl.

242
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,559
So why isn't this guy moving?

243
00:13:27,519 --> 00:13:30,000
Maybe it's cold and hibernating?

244
00:13:30,000 --> 00:13:30,840
Get the hell out of here.

245
00:13:36,279 --> 00:13:36,960
One.

246
00:13:37,960 --> 00:13:38,759
Two.

247
00:13:40,919 --> 00:13:41,600
Three.

248
00:13:47,039 --> 00:13:48,759
This guy sure isn't asleep.

249
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:50,399
What do we do now?

250
00:13:50,759 --> 00:13:52,200
We've got to find a way to lure it away.

251
00:13:52,559 --> 00:13:53,519
You're asking me?

252
00:13:53,519 --> 00:13:54,960
You're the Commander, you figure it out.

253
00:14:04,879 --> 00:14:05,679
One.

254
00:14:05,879 --> 00:14:06,679
Two.

255
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:07,639
Three.

256
00:14:08,240 --> 00:14:09,519
Hey buddy, over here!

257
00:14:19,679 --> 00:14:20,480
Old Chen!

258
00:14:26,080 --> 00:14:26,879
Old Chen!

259
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:29,759
Fatty!

260
00:14:37,480 --> 00:14:38,399
No, no, no!

261
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:39,679
Big guy, big guy!

262
00:15:21,840 --> 00:15:22,720
Officer He!

263
00:15:30,200 --> 00:15:31,159
Old White-Hair!

264
00:15:31,279 --> 00:15:33,080
Hurry, strike its vital spot!

265
00:15:47,600 --> 00:15:48,399
Old Chen!

266
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:49,879
Look, quick!
